      "content": "I hear how desperate you feel for relief, and it makes complete sense that advice like \"just ignore it\" feels useless when the pain is so overwhelming and persistent. The truth is that you don't have to force yourself to feel better alone; reaching out to a trusted adult, counselor, or mental health professional can provide the professional guidance you need to navigate this. There is no shame in admitting you're drowning, and seeking help is often the bravest way to find a real path out of this cycle.",
      "source": "target",
